Ukraine’s Spring Grain Plantings Climb 50%, Researcher Says

-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 
2011-03-25T10:17:40Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-25/ukraine-s-spring-grain-plantings-climb-50-researcher-says.html
Ukraine’s spring grain plantings
covered 253,000 hectares (624,910 acres) as of March 23, up 50
percent from a year earlier, according to data from APK-Inform.  Plantings were 169,000 hectares a year earlier, the
Dnipropetrovsk-based researcher said on its  website . Spring
barley was planted across 184,000 hectares and spring wheat on
2,000 hectares, APK said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
 kchoursina@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net  